.SH NAME
gnb-migrate - Import aliases from shell config files


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgnb migrate [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Scan your shell config files (.zshrc, .bashrc, config.fish) for existing
alias definitions and import them into ganbatte.

.PP
This is the fastest way to get started — bring all your existing aliases
into ganbatte with one command.

.PP
Example:
  gnb migrate
  gnb migrate --shell zsh
  gnb migrate --dry-run


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--dry-run\fP[=false]
	Preview without importing

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for migrate

.PP
\fB--shell\fP=""
	Shell type to scan (bash, zsh, fish). Auto-detected if omitted


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgnb(1)\fP


